00:33:28.520 --> 00:33:29.820
All right.

00:33:29.820 --> 00:33:34.470
So here's an example of the
security market line at work.

00:33:34.470 --> 00:33:37.530
And the slope of this
security market line

00:33:37.530 --> 00:33:40.050
is, of course, the expected
rate of return on the market

00:33:40.050 --> 00:33:41.640
minus the risk-free rate.

00:33:41.640 --> 00:33:44.160
And the idea behind the
security market line

00:33:44.160 --> 00:33:48.480
is that, no matter
what your beta is,

00:33:48.480 --> 00:33:50.790
you've got a required
rate of return that's

00:33:50.790 --> 00:33:52.740
determined by this slope.

00:33:52.740 --> 00:33:56.670
And now, to answer Eduard's
question about deviations

00:33:56.670 --> 00:33:59.610
and how far away you
are from efficiency

00:33:59.610 --> 00:34:04.320
if you deviate from this line,
then the vertical distance

00:34:04.320 --> 00:34:10.699
is the alpha of your portfolio
or project or investment

00:34:10.699 --> 00:34:12.260
opportunity.

00:34:12.260 --> 00:34:15.920
If markets are working
exactly the way they should,

00:34:15.920 --> 00:34:17.600
then you're on this line.

00:34:17.600 --> 00:34:19.900
You're always on this line.

00:34:19.900 --> 00:34:23.800
And if you're Warren Buffett,
you're off of this line.

00:34:23.800 --> 00:34:26.449
You've got a very
large, positive alpha.

00:34:26.449 --> 00:34:29.650
So if you've got skill, if
you can forecast markets,

00:34:29.650 --> 00:34:32.449
then you will do
better than this.

00:34:32.449 --> 00:34:35.650
But what this framework tells
you is that even if you cannot

00:34:35.650 --> 00:34:38.230
forecast markets, even if
you don't know what's going

00:34:38.230 --> 00:34:41.900
to happen next year
to stock prices,

00:34:41.900 --> 00:34:47.980
you should still do as well as
what this line suggests that

00:34:47.980 --> 00:34:48.980
you can do.

00:34:48.980 --> 00:34:49.480
OK?

00:34:49.480 --> 00:34:54.489
On average, this line should
be achievable by everybody

00:34:54.489 --> 00:34:58.190
that understands the
basics of portfolio theory.

00:34:58.190 --> 00:35:03.290
Now, as I said, the
performance evaluation approach

00:35:03.290 --> 00:35:05.720
to using the
security market line

00:35:05.720 --> 00:35:07.760
